//
// test/sema/resolution/dotted_func_def.test — dotted func-def form
// per N7 (T023 rollover; specs/006-m3-sema/tasks.md Phase 4a).
// Per N7 (lang.ebnf:1061), a dotted function definition like
// `func ic.ready { ... }` defines the body of a submodule's
// out-control terminal. Phase 3 ships head-only resolution; the
// fixture pins the parser+resolution shape so Phase 4b T058 / S20
// has a stable target.
//
// Per `emit-ast-format.contract.md` Invariants 2 + 3 (ASCII
// separators per Invariant 7).

// RUN: printf 'module m {\n  func ready {\n  }\n}\n' > %t.nsl
// RUN: %nslc -emit=ast %t.nsl | FileCheck %s

// CHECK: (ModuleBlock {{.*}}name=m
// CHECK: (FuncDefn {{.*}}name=ready
